# go2cs behavioral TargetComparison tests compare transpiled C# to .cs.target
# golden files BYTE-FOR-BYTE (TargetComparisonTests.FileMatch). The converter
# preserves the Go source's LF inside multi-line string literals, so these files
# legitimately contain mixed CRLF/LF. With core.autocrlf=true git would rewrite
# those LFs to CRLF on checkout and break the byte comparison. Mark the affected
# projects' transpiled output and goldens as binary so their exact bytes survive.
src/Tests/Behavioral/Solitaire/*.cs            -text
src/Tests/Behavioral/Solitaire/*.cs.target     -text
src/Tests/Behavioral/SortArrayType/*.cs        -text
src/Tests/Behavioral/SortArrayType/*.cs.target -text
src/Tests/Behavioral/StdLibInternalAbi/*.cs        -text
src/Tests/Behavioral/StdLibInternalAbi/*.cs.target -text
